<HEADLINE> Saints Sign Cowboys Punter  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas (AP) -- The New Orleans Saints signed Dallas
Cowboys restricted free-agent punter Toby Gowin to a three-year
offer sheet Tuesday. Terms weren't disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys, who tendered Gowin a one-year offer worth $472,000,
have seven days to match the Saints' contract or let him go. Dallas
wouldn't receive compensation if Gowin leaves because he signed as
an undrafted free agent out of North Texas in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas appear unwilling to match the offer, having signed two
punters within the last week.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas signed free agent Cory Collins and agreed to terms with
punter Barry Cantrell, who went to training camp with the Cowboys
last season. Both signed deals for the first-year minimum of
$178,000.
</P>
<P>
   Gowin averaged 43.2 yards per punt last season, finishing second
in the NFC and seventh in the NFL. He also handled kickoffs for the
Cowboys, finishing fifth in the NFC and seventh in the NFL with 12
touchbacks.
</P>
</TEXT>
