<HEADLINE> Stocks Open Lower; Nasdaq Down 135  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices opened lower on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average is down 75 points in early
trading. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a nearly
2-to-1 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 135 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down 16 points.
</P>
<P>
   The selling waves went around the globe overnight, returning to
Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
   Even though the Dow and the Nasdaq each had suffered intraday
losses of more than 500 points on Tuesday, they settled with just
double-digit declines.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow was down 57 points while the Nasdaq lost 74.
</P>
<P>
   But it was the most volatile trading ever for Wall Street, as
well as the busiest single day of trading on record.
</P>
<P>
   And markets have been losing ground across Europe following a
mostly lower session in Asia.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are higher.
</P>
</TEXT>
