<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 09:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man killed in logging accident in central New York  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HASTINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- A 20-year-old man walking through a wooded
area on his way to work was struck and killed by a falling tree,
state police said.
</P>
<P>
   Terry Warren II, of Central Square, was the victim on Tuesday of
a logging accident in the Oswego County Town of Hastings, troopers
said. He was walking near train tracks on his way to Buoy's
Restaurant in Brewerton.
</P>
<P>
   A crew from DK Enterprises had just finished cutting the 80-foot
tree, and it struck the Warren as it crashed to the ground.
</P>
<P>
   Warren heard the logger's warning and tried to get out of the
way, but inadvertently moved into the path of the tree, state
police Investigator Rick Hathaway.
</P>
<P>
   ''He just came up over the hill. My guy tried everything he
could,'' said David Kline, the company's owner. ''He was on posted
property. He wasn't supposed to be there.''
</P>
<P>
   Trooper Edward Foster said no criminal activity was involved in
Warren's death.
</P>
<P>
   ''In my 12 years with the state police, it's the first time I've
seen anything like this,'' Foster said.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, a state prison guard was killed while supervising an
inmate work crew that was clearing some woods in nearby Madison
County.
</P>
</TEXT>
