<HEADLINE> Arcadia Skeet Shoot Game Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Approximately 435,000 skeet shoot games are
being recalled by the manufacturer because of defective cartridges.
</P>
<P>
   The Consumer Product Safety Commission said Wednesday the
Arcadia Electronic Skeet Shoot game catridge may cause the
projector to overheat, melt and smoke. Game manufacturer Toymax
Inc., of Plainview, N.Y. has received 100 reports of this problem.
</P>
<P>
   The Arcadia Electronic Skeet Shoot game sets are indoor image
projecting game systems that include Duck Shoot and Deer Hunter
games. The game set includes a pump action rifle with a simulated
laser scope and realistic shooting sounds when fired.
</P>
<P>
   The Duck Shoot Game has a gray rifle and projector, and the Deer
Hunter game has a camouflage rifle and projector. Meteor Attack and
Fighter Attack cartridges, sold separately, are also included in
the recall. The Meteor Attack cartridge is silver and the Fighter
Attack cartridge is black.
</P>
<P>
   ''ARCADIA ELECTRONIC SKEET SHOOT'' is written on a label on the
projector, and writing on the bottom of the projector includes
''1998 TOYMAX,'' ''PATENT PENDING,'' and ''MADE IN CHINA.''
</P>
<P>
   Toy and discount department stores nationwide, including Toys R
Us, Sam's Club, KB Toys and Costco, sold the games from October
1998 through March of this year for about $65.
</P>
<P>
   Customers should immediately stop using the games and remove the
game cartridge from the console. To receive a free replacement
cartridge or for more information, customers can contact Toymax at
(800) 477-6215 anytime, or visit the company web site,
www.toymax.com. Customers should not return the games or cartridges
to stores.
</P>
<P>
   New and replacement game cartridges are orange. All Arcadia
Electronic Skeet Shoot game cartridges that are not orange should
be replaced.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   Toymax: http://www.toymax.com
</P>
<P>
   Consumer Product Safety Commission: http://www.cpsc.gov
</P>
</TEXT>
