<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Sears, Roebuck and Co., up 6 13/16 at 37 5/16
</P>
<P>
   Sears said its first-quarter earnings should come in between 62
cents and 67 cents per share, well above analysts' forecasts of 46
cents. Sears cited strength in retail, its credit business and its
Sears Canada Inc. unit, as well as a reduction in the number of
shares outstanding.
</P>
<P>
MetLife Inc., priced at 14\, trading at 15[
</P>
<P>
   The nation's second-largest life insurer raised $2.88 billion
after pricing its initial public offering as the company converts
to a public company from one owned by policyholders. The IPO was
scaled back considerably from the company's original plans.
</P>
