</P>
<P>
Carey International Inc., down 7 15/32 at 9 19/32
</P>
<P>
   The chauffeur provider earned $1 million, or 10 cents per share,
in the first quarter, down from $1.7 million, or 17 cents per
share, in last year's first quarter. Carey blamed added investments
in personnel, infrastructure and subcontracting as a result of
growth and increased demand.
</P>
<P>
Onyx Software Corp., up 3\ at 27
</P>
<P>
   The company launched two new Internet portals which allow
business clients to handle some customer-service functions online.
Onyx makes software and other products used in the electronic
commerce industry.
</P>
<P>
Foamex International Inc., down 1| at 6]
</P>
<P>
   The maker of flexible polyurethane and polymer foam products
said discussions with a potential buyer have ended. Foamex didn't
say why the talks ended, but said it plans to continue evaluating
strategic options.
</P>
