<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 18:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vanguard 500 Eclipses Magellan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Vanguard Group's Index 500 fund apparently
eclipsed Fidelity's flagship Magellan fund as the largest mutual
fund in terms of total assets -- at least temporarily, according to
reports Wednesday from two newsletters that track the funds.
</P>
<P>
   James Lowell, editor of ''Fidelity Investor,'' and Daniel
Wiener, editor of ''Independent Adviser for Vanguard Investors,''
claim in their reports that the Vanguard Index fund had $107.2
billion in funds as of Tuesday, compared with $106.9 billion in the
Magellan fund.
</P>
<P>
   The size of the two funds has been watched closely by analysts
because the two represent different investment strategies: low-cost
passive management vs. higher-cost active management.
</P>
<P>
   The low-cost Vanguard fund requires little management because
its goal is simply to mirror the performance of the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500-stock index. The Magellan fund is actively managed,
usually by well-paid, high-profile fund managers.
</P>
<P>
   The two newsletter editors based their findings on historical
cash flows into the two funds. In addition, the two used stock
market performance through Tuesday to determine each fund's assets,
according to a joint statement issued by the editors.
</P>
<P>
   A Vanguard spokesman said he couldn't confirm that the Index 500
fund had surpassed Magellan in assets. But the spokesman said the
fund had $107.4 billion in assets at the end of March.
</P>
<P>
   In statement issued after the reports surfaced, Vanguard
Chairman John Brennan issued a statement saying, in part, ''We are
gratified that our shareholders have embraced indexing as an
investment strategy.''
</P>
<P>
   Brennan added that Vanguard believes it's ''irrelevant'' to
focus on the size of a mutual fund.
</P>
<P>
   Fidelity officials could not be reached for comment. A phone
call seeking comment was not immediately returned.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Web: www.Vanguard.com; www.Fidelity.com;
www.FidelityInvestor.com and www.AdviserOnline.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
