<HEADLINE> RETRANSMITS to fix typo in overline  </HEADLINE>
By LARRY NEUMEISTER, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Prospective jurors in the case of a former Wall
Street executive accused of trading stock secrets with an X-rated
movie star faced a tough question themselves Wednesday: Do you have
any opinions about extramarital affairs that could affect your
judgment?
</P>
<P>
   The question was 36th on a list of 42 posed to each potential
juror at the start of the Manhattan trial of James McDermott Jr.,
the former chief executive officer at Keefe, Bruyette &AMP; Woods. By
the end of the day, a jury had been chosen in U.S. District Court.
</P>
<P>
   ''You will hear evidence in this case about an extramarital
affair. Is there anything about extramarital affairs, or a person
who has had one, which might affect your ability to be fair and
impartial, or which might otherwise make it difficult for you to
serve as a juror?''
</P>
<P>
   The first prospective juror to be asked the question publicly
said, ''Extramarital affairs are wrong but not illegal.''
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors in the case have not said it was illegal for
McDermott to engage in an affair with Kathryn Gannon, who went by
the name Marylin Star in the adult entertainment business. But they
have alleged in pretrial arguments that his desire to impress
Gannon might have influenced him to feed her inside information
about impending mergers and acquisitions.
</P>
<P>
   Gannon, a fugitive in the case, then allegedly gave the tips to
a friend, Anthony P. Pomponio, who is on trial with McDermott.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors wanted to tell the jury when opening statements
begin Monday about Gannon's career, but Judge Kimba Wood has
decided Gannon will be referred to only as a model, dancer and
actress.
</P>
<P>
   McDermott, Pomponio and Gannon are each charged with conspiracy
and securities fraud. Prosecutors allege the trio made more than
$170,000 in illegal profits.
</P>
<P>
   McDermott, 48, of Briarcliff Manor, and Pomponio, 45, of North
Caldwell, N.J., remain free on bail. Gannon, 30, formerly of Miami,
Fla., is believed to be living in Canada, and prosecutors are
seeking her extradition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
