<HEADLINE> AP Names Tanner Medical Writer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Lindsey Tanner, a veteran reporter and editor in
the Chicago bureau of The Associated Press, has been named a
medical writer based here.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Chief of Bureau James
Reindl.
</P>
<P>
   Tanner joined the AP in Chicago in 1984. She won a Peter Lisagor
Award from the Chicago Headline Club for feature writing in 1991
and is a three-time winner of the Charles Chamberlain Award given
by the Illinois Associated Press Editors Association for
outstanding writing.
</P>
<P>
   She is a graduate of the University of California-Los Angeles
and Northwestern University.
</P>
<P>
   Tanner, 42, succeeds Brenda Coleman, who resigned.
</P>
