<HEADLINE> Four Teens Killed in Wis. Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RHINELANDER, Wis. (AP) -- Four teen-agers were killed when their
car ran off a road and crashed into a driveway embankment,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the Tuesday night accident, about 100 miles
northwest of Green Bay, was being investigated, the Oneida County
Sheriff's Department said. Neither alcohol nor excessive speed
appeared to be a factor, Sheriff Timothy Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   The victims attended Rhinelander High School, said Principal Jim
Gehrke.
</P>
<P>
   Robin Steffke, an 16-year-old junior, was at the wheel when the
car went onto the shoulder, skidded across the road, hit the
embankment and flipped on its roof, Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   Also killed were Richard L. Blackburn, an 18-year-old junior;
and freshmen Corry Jefferson, 15, and Adam J. Ring, 15, Miller
said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Everybody is sad and crying,'' Samantha Jefferson, a friend of
two of the victims, said Wednesday. ''When I got to school today,
everybody was devastated; many went home.''
</P>
<P>
   Counselors were available Wednesday for the 1,140 students at
the school.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's my 36th year as a school person, and I guess I've never
seen this many tears,'' Gehrke said.
</P>
</TEXT>
