<HEADLINE> Buchanan Wants Troops Out of Europe  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Reform Party presidential candidate Pat
Buchanan says he is running for president to give voters a new
option.
</P>
<P>
   ''Unless I ran as the Reform Party candidate, Americans would
not have a real choice,'' he told about 60 people Wednesday at a
reception in Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   Buchanan said he differs from the Republican and Democratic
candidates on free trade, immigration and the World Trade
Organization -- which he says the United States should never have
joined.
</P>
<P>
   He said China should not be given permanent normal trade status
unless its government ''stops persecuting Christians'' and drops
threats against the United States and Taiwan. Buchanan also
suggested that the American troops be pulled out of Bosnia and
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think it's time we defended the borders of our own
country,'' he said.
</P>
