<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-05 22:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CKE Reports 4Q Loss  </HEADLINE>
By GARY GENTILE, AP Business Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- CKE Restaurants said Wednesday it lost $61.8
million in its fourth quarter and is talking to investment bankers
about how to stem mounting losses from its 1998 purchase of the
Hardee's chain.
</P>
<P>
   The loss of $1.22 per share was due to lagging sales at Hardee's
outlets and costs associated with a restaurant makeover effort, CKE
said.
</P>
<P>
   The company reported net income of $13.5 million, or 26 cents
per share, for the fourth quarter last year. This year's fourth
quarter, which ended Jan. 31, was a week longer than last year's.
</P>
<P>
   The company also reported a loss of $29.1 million, or 56 cents
per share, for the year, compared with net income of $77.7 million,
or $1.45 per share, last year.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are deeply disappointed with our overall results for the
quarter and the fiscal year,'' Tom Thompson, CKE's president and
chief executive officer, said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   In a conference call for stock analysts, Thompson blamed the
losses on two failed advertising campaigns, a decision to bear the
brunt of the costs for remodeling older restaurants and
difficulties in consolidating administration of the Hardee's chain,
based primarily in the east, with the company's California-based
Carl's Jr. chain.
</P>
<P>
   CKE said it is in the initial stages of ''evaluating strategic
alternatives'' regarding Hardee's.
</P>
<P>
   ''We think it's the right thing to do to explore other options
and have a contingency plan just in case,'' a company spokesperson
said, adding that selling the chain is among the range of options.
</P>
<P>
   Thompson said the company has high hopes for its effort to
convert many of its older Hardee's locations into ''Star Hardee's''
restaurants -- a hybrid Carl's Jr. and Hardee's. Over the past year,
the company has shouldered most of the cost of those conversions, a
decision Thompson said, ''compounded the turnaround challenge.''
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter, CKE began franchising more of its
company-owned Hardee's restaurants and Thompson said continued
sales should help the company return to profitability.
</P>
<P>
   CKE sold 83 restaurants in the fourth quarter for a one-time
gain of $40 million. Thompson said the strategy should generate
another $200 million in the next fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
   Same-store sales at the flagship Carl's Jr. outlets increased
1.5 percent, which includes both the company-owned and franchised
outlets. Same-store sales at Taco Bueno stores increased 1.8
percent. Those gains were offset by a drop in same-store sales at
company-owned and franchised Hardee's stores of 3.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
   CKE's stock lost 93} cents, ending at $5.18} on the New York
Stock Exchange on Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-05-00 2212 </TRAILER>
