<HEADLINE> Penguins 4, Maple Leafs 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Jaromir Jagr tallied two goals and an assist as
the Pittsburgh Penguins beat the Toronto Maple Leafs 4-2 Wednesday
night to clinch a playoff berth.
</P>
<P>
   Rob Brown and Robert Lang also scored for Pittsburgh, while Ron
Tugnutt made 31 saves.
</P>
<P>
   Pittsburgh, seventh in the Eastern Conference with 86 points, is
five points ahead of both Montreal and Buffalo, and six ahead of
Carolina. Buffalo has three games left, while Montreal and Carolina
each have two.
</P>
<P>
   The Leafs failed for the second successive game to clinch their
first division title since 1962-63. Toronto is five points head of
Ottawa in the Northeast Division. The Leafs have two games left and
Ottawa three.
</P>
<P>
   Kris King and Steve Thomas scored for Toronto, but Jagr turned a
2-1 deficit into a 3-2 Penguins lead after two periods.
</P>
<P>
   The winger ripped a shot from a bad angle past Curtis Joseph at
8:13 of the second period on a power play and scored again with
1:35 left in the period when he one-timed a pass from Jan Hrdina.
</P>
<P>
   Lang gave Pittsburgh a two-goal lead 1:14 into the third when he
turned in a Jagr pass.
</P>
<P>
   Toronto held a two-man advantage for 1:46 of the third period,
but could not convert.
</P>
<P>
   King opened the scoring midway through the first period when
Kevyn Adams fanned on a shot, leaving King with an open net.
</P>
<P>
   Brown replied for the Penguins when he brought the puck out from
behind the Leafs' net and jammed it past Joseph at 13:31.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas put the Leafs back in front 50 seconds later when he
gathered the puck and sent it home after Jonas Hoglund fanned on a
shot.
</P>
</TEXT>
