<HEADLINE> Red Wings Sign Shanahan for 4 Years  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- All-Star left wing Brendan Shanahan signed a
four-year contract with the Detroit Red Wings on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Brendan has been a very large part of this club's success
since we acquired him in the 1996-97 season,'' general manager Ken
Holland.
</P>
<P>
   Neither the team nor Shanahan's agent, Rick Curran, would
disclose terms of the contract. The Detroit News and Detroit Free
Press reported the contract is worth $26 million and contains a
no-trade clause.
</P>
<P>
   ''I am happy here,'' Shanahan told the Free Press. ''All the
players that come here can't believe what a great hockey town this
is. ... I like what we've built here.''
</P>
<P>
   Shanahan, 31, has 77 points and leads the team with 40 goals
going into Friday's game against Washington. He is being paid $4
million this season.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-3, 215-pound native of Mimico, Ontario, is currently
the 10th-leading scorer in the NHL. His career points total 878 in
945 games.
</P>
<P>
   Shanahan, who became a Red Wing in October 1996, would have been
an unrestricted free agent at the end of the season.
</P>
